7. That Mary told the Deponent, that the Night Hogg's Goods were ſtolen, Caeſar was aſleep upon the Table; 
                           〈◊〉
                         he had been drinking very hard, and John Hughſon came to him about Eleven o'Clock and waked him, and ſaid to him, You forget your Promiſe, don't you? Caeſar anſwered, No, Sir, I don't, and thereupon get up and went out; and then Hughſon ſent Mary to Bed; and Mary ſaid, that upon, this ſhe ſuſpected ſomething extraordinary was to be done, ſhe could not ſleep; and ſhe heard the Noiſe when they brought the Goods, which ſhe took to be about Twelve or One o'Clock.
